CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 10, 1952, pg. 17 reads: "Star Of The West Lodge Entertains - Star of The West Lodge Entertains - Star of the West Lodge 62 recently celebrated at the Masonic Lodge by entertaining their wives and sweethearts with a buffet dinner. Their honored guests were the Stars of Judah, their adopted sisters; the grand lecturer, and Worthy Matron Mary Smith and Brother James Smith.  Morris Fountain was chairman of the affair. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of the Star of the West Lodge 62, with wives and sweethearts, gathered in Masonic Lodge for buffet dinner
